@Mean Old Lady - I had always thought of California as a land of perpetual natural disasters. In the mid-80s I was invited to go out there and play a recital in San Diego (they have a lovely outdoor pipe organ in Balboa Park), and have my first experience of California in reality.

Leading up to the date, record-breaking drought, wildfires, followed by record-breaking rainfall, mudslides, floods, windfallen trees, and the day before my recital, an earthquake that dislodged many pipes in the two organs I was scheduled to play that week.

I flew home via a hop to Los Angeles, where I watched the wing of the plane splitting the brown air into rivulets of sludge. Never been tempted to call California home.

